Launch an EC2 instance using that key
Attach the key pair to the instance so it will accept your private key for SSH.

In EC2, click Instances → Launch instances

Choose an AMI (e.g., Amazon Linux 2 or Ubuntu)

Pick an instance type (e.g., t2.micro)

Under Key pair (login) select your key (e.g., soc-ec2-key)

Ensure the security group allows SSH (port 22) from your IP

Click Launch instance and wait until its state is running
